events.description: The release of Austria's trade balance figures for November 2025, showing a narrowing deficit.

facts.fact_text: Austria's trade deficit narrowed to EUR 0.35 billion in November 2025.

evidences.evidence_text: Austria's trade deficit narrowed slightly to EUR 0.35 billion in November 2025 from EUR 0.37 billion in the corresponding month of the previous year

facts.fact_text: Exports increased 1.3% year-on-year to EUR 16.45 billion in November.

evidences.evidence_text: Exports increased 1.3% year-on-year to EUR 16.45 billion

facts.fact_text: Imports rose 1.2% to EUR 16.80 billion in November.

evidences.evidence_text: Meanwhile, imports rose 1.2% to EUR 16.80 billion

facts.fact_text: Austria recorded a trade deficit of EUR 5.10 billion for the first eleven months of 2025.

evidences.evidence_text: Considering the first eleven months of the year, Austria recorded an overall trade deficit of EUR 5.10 billion, shifting from a surplus of EUR 2.51 billion in the same period last year.

claims.claim_text: The narrowing of the trade deficit in November was caused by exports rising faster than imports.

evidences.evidence_text: Austria's trade deficit narrowed slightly... as exports rose more than imports.

claims.claim_text: Export growth in November was driven by increased sales to both EU and non-EU markets.

evidences.evidence_text: driven by higher sales to both EU countries (1.4%) and non-EU countries (1.3%).

evidence.evidence_text: Exports increased 1.3% year-on-year to EUR 16.45 billion, driven by higher sales to both EU countries (1.4%) and non-EU countries (1.3%).
Austria's trade deficit narrowed slightly... as exports rose more than imports.
Austria recorded an overall trade deficit of EUR 5.10 billion, shifting from a surplus of EUR 2.51 billion in the same period last year.
